        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2159783384" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7984446271109385340">This book is not my cup of tea.<br/><br/>The stories are told in a rapid-sketched, cartoonish style, reminiscent of Vonnegut but without any of the humor or hope.<br/><br/>In the introductions to the various stories, the author mentions that most of them were first published in &quot;girlie&quot; magazines because, he says, they don&apos;t &quot;edit&quot; him. Having finished this collection I have to wonder if it didn&apos;t also have something to do with the way Ellison portrays women in this collection: as objects. Things to be feared, or d</span>
  <span id="freeText7984446271109385340" style="display:none">This book is not my cup of tea.<br /><br />The stories are told in a rapid-sketched, cartoonish style, reminiscent of Vonnegut but without any of the humor or hope.<br /><br />In the introductions to the various stories, the author mentions that most of them were first published in "girlie" magazines because, he says, they don't "edit" him. Having finished this collection I have to wonder if it didn't also have something to do with the way Ellison portrays women in this collection: as objects. Things to be feared, or desired, or both. <br /><br />This guy seems to have been in a really bad head-space when he wrote this stuff.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7984446271109385340" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
