      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rachel Bea" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rachel Bea" href="/user/show/2805400-rachel-bea">Rachel Bea</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781497609617" href="/book/show/22308929-i-have-no-mouth-and-i-must-scream">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2805400-rachel-bea?shelf=books-of-2019">books-of-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2805400-rachel-bea?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2652218121" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1879596222784405349">Meh. The misogyny that ran throughout the stories was... really off-putting. For example it&apos;s hard to enjoy a story when a woman character is being blamed for getting sexually assaulted. It&apos;s too bad the stories include gross crap like that because otherwise they would have been pretty good. The imagery coming from the text was nightmare-ish and disturbing. So, I liked that aspect of the stories. The writing was otherwise good to okay. I&apos;ve been intrigued by this collection for a while now but I</span>
  <span id="freeText1879596222784405349" style="display:none">Meh. The misogyny that ran throughout the stories was... really off-putting. For example it's hard to enjoy a story when a woman character is being blamed for getting sexually assaulted. It's too bad the stories include gross crap like that because otherwise they would have been pretty good. The imagery coming from the text was nightmare-ish and disturbing. So, I liked that aspect of the stories. The writing was otherwise good to okay. I've been intrigued by this collection for a while now but I don't think it lived up to the hype I had for it in my head. <br /><br />Also, my copy had this weird thing where before each story there was a short introduction. But none of the introductions were complete; they all ended like in the middle of a sentence. No idea what's up with that.</span>
